`` All the positive figures on the economy are out already , and people are focusing more on the dangers for next year , mostly the wage talks and the -LCB- parliamentary -RCB- elections , '' the U.S. trader said .
The market also shrugged off positive factors , such as higher bond prices and a slowdown in monetary growth in September , traders said .
They said they expect the bearish mood to persist a while longer , as trading volume is falling toward the end of the year and the market is becoming more volatile .
