At 3.8 million won , or $ 5,700 , the econobox is the lowest-priced car in South Korea .
Ford Motor Co. and Japan 's Mazda Motor Corp. have equity interests in Kia .
Loans for as long as five years make the cars very accessible , with monthly payments as low as 80,000 won , or $ 120 .
Daewoo Motor , a 50-50 joint venture with General Motors Corp. and the Daewoo Group conglomerate , is the only auto maker that appears to be hurting .
